+## About This Repository
+
+The purpose of this repository is to make the source code for Cardinal's
+self-hosted apps available to users for inspect.
+
+This is however not the repository where work actively happens. This repository
+is a read-only clone of Cardinal's main (private) repository, but with only the
+self-hosted packages included.
+
+<details>
+ <summary>About the commit history</summary>
+ The original commits from the main repo cannot be preserved because they contain references to files that don't exist in this clone. So, the Cardinal CI bot generates new commits with only the changes for the files in this repository.
+</details>
+
+<details>
+ <summary>How do I build the apps?</summary>
+ Official builds are distributed by Cardinal Apps Inc. and are available on <a href="https://hub.docker.com/r/cardinalapps/media-server">Docker Hub</a>. Building these images is a multi-stage process that is handled by Cardinal's CI. All of the build scripts are available in this repository, but the orchestration is not.
+</details>
+
+<details>
+ <summary>Contributing</summary>
+ We are not currently taking code contributions from the general public. You may still create an issue to report a bug or make a feature request. You can also join <a href="https://discord.gg/WWXngggPp4">Docker Hub</a> to share your opinion.
+</details>
 
